properties.description: // Product cut & sewn by inmates at Vanaja prison located in Hämeenlinna, Finland. The factory employs around 15 female prisoners who are trained by skillful professionals to do a wide range of clothing and textile production. The main aim for the Vanaja prison is preparing the inmates for freedom which the daily work at the sewing factory supports.
